        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Purpose"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "The Trust will provide an effective escalation policy to enhance the care of"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "acutely ill and potentially deteriorating patients in Braintree community hospital. It will support the appropriate and prompt management of"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "patients at risk of deterioration, thereby reducing clinical risk and enhancing patients care."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.2,
                "text": "The purpose of this document is to ensure that the National Early Warning Score (NEWS) system alerts staff to recognise acutely/critically ill patients early and enable them to initiate prompt and appropriate action to manage these patients."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.3,
                "text": "It will ensure that the different levels of Nursing and Clinical staff are utilised appropriately in the management of acutely unwell patients."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.4,
                "text": "This policy outlines the operational arrangements for the BCH Staff. It includes a locally customized NEWS tool which has been developed and implemented as a result of the resources available at BCH. The goal of this policy is to:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Helps reduce the risk to patients by early intervention."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Assists staff to identify signs of deterioration and trigger Senior review."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A tool to guide appropriate responses and management of patients and initiate the patient transfer pathway where appropriate."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Includes standards for the recording of nursing observations on wards."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.5,
                "text": "To promote the NEWS treatment and escalation policy with all members of the multidisciplinary team to enable them to recognise and effectively treat patients at risk of deterioration within the BCH wards area and identify those patients they may need to be transferred to a higher level of care."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.6,
                "text": "To identify training and support needs and ensure that these are put into place."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 24.0,
                "text": "The deteriorating patient policy will apply to all patients cared for at Braintree Community Hospital and will be effective  hours a day."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Responsibilities"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.1,
                "text": "Managing Director is responsible for ensuring that the policy is in place."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.2,
                "text": "Director of Nursing is co-responsible for the development of the policy and its implementation."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.3,
                "text": "Medical Director is co-responsible for the development of the policy and its effectiveness"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.4,
                "text": "Director of Nursing and Clinical Lead Consultants are responsible for ensuring that the policy is implemented and monitored."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "BCH Escalation Policy:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "All staff performing observations at BCH must adhere to the following escalation criteria for patients. This includes:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "\u25cf Perform observations within the desired time frame governed by the patient's clinical condition and the pre-set time frames within the escalation policy."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "\u25cf Contact the appropriate level of clinician associated with the patients NEWS score and request the appropriate clinical response."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "\u25cf Document clearly in the patients notes any escalation concerns and the outcomes of review."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "\u25cf Perform periodical audit to demonstrate the numbers of patients that require escalation and draw conclusions from the data to try to develop future service improvement."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 43,
            "data": {
                "url": "19024 Adult Observation Policy for Braintree Community Hospital (BCH) 1.0.003.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
