                "url": "19024 Adult Observation Policy for Braintree Community Hospital (BCH) 1.0.005.jpeg"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "Training will be delivered initially by TaRT team and then cascade training can then take place by members of the Orthopaedic Team."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "A log of all staff who have received training will be kept by the Lead Nurse."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "The Staff will undertake mandatory training regarding Resuscitation and Managing the deteriorating patient in accordance with Trust policy."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "All patients within the operational areas who trigger on NEWS, or who gives cause for concern can be referred to the RMO +/- the on-call Orthopaedic Consultant."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 50,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.1,
                "text": "All clinical incidents and breaches of this policy will be reported via a trust risk event form and investigated in accordance with Trust policy."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 8.0,
                "text": "Audit & Monitoring"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 8.1,
                "text": "Audit of NEWS will take place on a quarterly basis and the results communicated through the DPG (Deteriorating Patient Group) and the individual divisional groups reports."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 54,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 8.2,
                "text": "The DPG discusses issues surrounding NEWS and the escalation. It reviews audits and compliance to the policy"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 55,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 8.3,
                "text": "Any incidents or concerns are reported to the DPG meeting held monthly."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 56,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Issues from the meeting are then reported at the Patient Safety Group (PSG)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 57,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 9.0,
                "text": "Implementation"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 58,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 9.1,
                "text": "This policy will be published on the Intranet and website"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 59,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 9.2,
                "text": "It is the responsibility of the author to ensure that all clinical staff are made aware of the policy either by email or at directorate meetings."
            }
        },
